<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; color:#000000; bEditID:r3st1; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<p>Dear {!Contact.FirstName},</p><p><br></p><p>Welcome to the Copado Family.</p><p><br></p><p>We hope you will enjoy the use of Copado and Copado Change Management.</p><p><br></p><p>To get you started, I have included a few instructions below that will need to be executed to complete the setup of Copado (some steps may have already been completed).</p><p><br></p><ol><li>If you have not already, use the&nbsp;following link to install Copado into your Production Environment: <a href="http://www.copa.do/install">http://www.copa.do/install</a></li><li>As soon as Copado has been installed click on the Account Summary Tab so that your Org is registered on our servers.</li><li>Navigate to Setup - Company Profile&nbsp;- Company Information and send us your Salesforce Org Id,&nbsp;so that we can provision the licenses and activate all your features.</li><li>If you have ordered a mix of licenses (Copado Change Management &amp; Copado, and/or Selenium Testing) you will need to set up those users using the&nbsp;<a href="http://docs.copa.do/copado/copado-license-manager">Copado License Manager</a>&nbsp;tab.&nbsp; Detailed instructions are&nbsp;<a href="http://docs.copa.do/copado/copado-license-manager">here</a>.</li><li>Now we need to setup your first Org Credential.</li><ol><li>Click on the Org Credential Tab &amp; press the New button.</li><li>Name your Org Credential (We suggest adding your initials as a pre-fix). E.g. "PR Production" or "PR Copado Org" and press Save.</li><li>Press the "Set OAuth Authentication" button.</li><li>Enter the Username that you have used to login to the Org where you installed Copado, enter the password and press Login.</li><li>Allow Copado to connect to your Salesforce org.</li><li>You will be directed to the Org Credential page.</li></ol><li>Once we have activated all the features (you will receive an email from us), click on the "Account Summary" tab.</li><li>From the Account Summary tab, press the sub-tab "Features" and then press, "Sync Features". (NOTE: Your credits/features might now show immediately until they are provisioned and synced).</li><li>The Setup process is complete.&nbsp; </li></ol><p>If you have any questions regarding the above, please feel free to email <a href="mailto:support@copa.do">support@copa.do</a> and I will be happy to guide you through the process.</p><p><br></p><p>Kind regards,</p><p><br></p><p>{!User.FirstName}</p>]]></td>
